1. Why did I use GROMACS ?
GROMACS (GROningen MAchine for Chemical Simulations) is one of the most widely used molecular dynamics engines in the world, and for good reasons:
Speed and Efficiency:Can simulate large protein-ligand systems faster than most other MD engines while maintaining accuracy.
Open-Source and Free
Flexibility and Compatibility: supports a wide range of force fields, solvents, and constraints, compatible with standard topology generators (pdb2gmx, ACPYPE, CGenFF), can handle complex protein-ligand, membrane, and nucleic acid systems.

Strong Community and Documentation: Extensive tutorials and user forums make troubleshooting easier and active development ensures stability, bug fixes, and performance improvements.

Reproducibility: deterministic algorithms and checkpointing allow reproducible runs, which is critical for research and publication.
