| **Protein Accuracy**               | Updated backbone & side-chain parameters; highly accurate | Accurate, but older versions may deviate for certain loops | Moderate; side-chain accuracy can vary               | Less accurate for modern ligands     |
| **Ligand Compatibility**           | Seamless with CGenFF for drug-like ligands                | Needs Antechamber; careful parameterization                | Compatible but sometimes requires manual adjustments | Ligand support limited               |
| **Ion & Water Models**             | Modern updates, more stable in EM/MD                      | Accurate, but fewer updates for ions                       | Standard models, may need tuning                     | Older models, less realistic         |
| **Stability in EM/MD**             | Less prone to LINCS or extreme force failures             | Generally stable                                           | Stable, but slower EM convergence                    | Can be unstable with small molecules |
| **Community & Literature Support** | Widely validated; latest 2022 updates                     | Extensive, many publications                               | Moderate                                             | Limited, mostly legacy studies       |
| **Future-Proof**                   | Ready for enhanced sampling, free energy calculations     | Good, but may require older AMBER updates                  | Moderate                                             | Limited for advanced simulations     |

